<section id="about" class="fade-in">
  <span class="sec-lbl" id="lAbout">About Kerala</span>
  <h2 class="sec-title" id="aboutTitle">God's Own <em>Country</em></h2>
  <p class="sec-body" id="aboutBody">Kerala, fondly called "God's Own Country," is India's southernmost state on the Arabian Sea coast. A land of pristine backwaters, emerald rice paddies, and spice-scented winds, Kerala stands out with its high literacy rate, healthcare standards, and social development. Once the spice capital that attracted traders from across the world, Kerala retains its mystique through coconut palms, tea gardens, and beaches. Home to ancient mosques, synagogues, Hindu temples, and Christian churches coexisting peacefully, Kerala embodies spiritual pluralism. With its exceptional biodiversity, ayurvedic traditions, and cuisine that blends tradition with international influence, Kerala offers a unique blend of natural beauty, cultural richness, and modern consciousness.</p>
</section>

